    "content": "Web search results for query: \"OpenAI Whisper limit language detection to specific languages auto detect English Bulgarian only\"\n\nI'll search for information about limiting OpenAI Whisper's language detection to specific languages, particularly English and Bulgarian.\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"wrong language detection and forcing the right one · openai/whisper · Discussion #529\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/openai/whisper/discussions/529\"},{\"title\":\"Make language detection only includes 2 languages? · openai/whisper · Discussion #849\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/openai/whisper/discussions/849\"},{\"title\":\"Whisper language recognition - Documentation - OpenAI Developer Community\",\"url\":\"https://community.openai.com/t/whisper-language-recognition/665358\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - openai/whisper: Robust Speech Recognition via Large-Scale Weak Supervision\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/openai/whisper\"},{\"title\":\"Introducing Whisper | OpenAI\",\"url\":\"https://openai.com/index/whisper/\"},{\"title\":\"Language Detection using large-v3 · openai/whisper · Discussion #2167\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/openai/whisper/discussions/2167\"},{\"title\":\"[Whisper] Is there a way to tell the language before recognition? - API - OpenAI Developer Community\",\"url\":\"https://community.openai.com/t/whisper-is-there-a-way-to-tell-the-language-before-recognition/70687\"},{\"title\":\"whisper/README.md at main · openai/whisper\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/openai/whisper/blob/main/README.md\"},{\"title\":\"Exclude detection of certain languages or detect only one particular language · openai/whisper · Discussion #1549\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/openai/whisper/discussions/1549\"},{\"title\":\"Audio API FAQ | OpenAI Help Center\",\"url\":\"https://help.openai.com/en/articles/7031512-whisper-audio-api-faq\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about limiting OpenAI Whisper's language detection to specific languages like English and Bulgarian:\n\n## Key Findings:\n\n### Current Limitations\nWhisper currently doesn't support providing a list of languages to limit detection to specific languages. Users have requested features to make the model recognize/detect only specific languages (e.g., bilingual French & English) because with language=None, incorrect language detection can occur.\n\n### Available Workarounds:\n\n1. **Force a Single Language**: You can use the '--language' parameter to force a specific language and skip auto-detection. For example, you can use `--language en` for English or `--language bg` for Bulgarian. The supported language codes include 'bg' for Bulgarian and 'en' for English among many others.\n\n2. **Transcribe Multiple Times**: If your audio has both English and another language in the same file, you need to transcribe twice, once for each language, using the --language flag.\n\n3. **Language Detection Issues**: Whisper detects language using the first 30 seconds of audio if you don't specify one, which can lead to incorrect detection. When you specify language='en', you are actually disabling detection and telling it to assume English.\n\n### Practical Solutions for English/Bulgarian:\n\nSince Whisper doesn't natively support limiting detection to just English and Bulgarian, you have these options:\n\n1. **Manual Detection + Forced Transcription**: You could detect the languages in the audio using some other service, and then transcribe chunk by chunk with the appropriate language specified.\n\n2. **Post-Processing Approach**: For audio with multiple languages, transcribe the audio in both languages separately and then do post-processing to combine results.\n\n3. **Speaker Diarization Method**: Use speaker diarization tools like pyannote to identify different speakers and their time segments, then use Whisper to detect language separately for each audio segment.\n\nUnfortunately, there's no built-in way to restrict Whisper's auto-detection to only English and Bulgarian. The most reliable approach would be to either force one language at a time or implement a custom solution that processes the audio multiple times with different language settings."
