he bot on login:\n    70→\n    71→1. Create the plist file:\n    72→```bash\n    73→cat > ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.user.telegram-voice-bot.plist << 'EOF'\n    74→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n    75→<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC \"-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN\" \"http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd\">\n    76→<plist version=\"1.0\">\n    77→<dict>\n    78→    <key>Label</key>\n    79→    <string>com.user.telegram-voice-bot</string>\n    80→    \n    81→    <key>ProgramArguments</key>\n    82→    <array>\n    83→        <string>/usr/bin/env</string>\n    84→        <string>uv</string>\n    85→        <string>run</string>\n    86→        <string>python</string>\n    87→        <string>bot.py</string>\n    88→    </array>\n    89→    \n    90→    <key>WorkingDirectory</key>\n    91→    <string>/Users/yabo/Documents/Code/phone-to-laptop</string>\n    92→    \n    93→    <key>RunAtLoad</key>\n    94→    <true/>\n    95→    \n    96→    <key>KeepAlive</key>\n    97→    <true/>\n    98→    \n    99→    <key>StandardOutPath</key>\n   100→    <string>/Users/yabo/Documents/Code/phone-to-laptop/logs/launchd.out.log</string>\n   101→    \n   102→    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>\n   103→    <string>/Users/yabo/Documents/Code/phone-to-laptop/logs/launchd.err.log</string>\n   104→</dict>\n   105→</plist>\n   106→EOF\n   107→```\n   108→\n   109→2. Load the service:\n   110→```bash\n   111→launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.user.telegram-voice-bot.plist\n   112→```\n   113→\n   114→3. Start the service:\n   115→```bash\n   116→launchctl start com.user.telegram-voice-bot\n   117→```\n   118→\n   119→4. Check status:\n   120→```bash\n   121→launchctl list | grep telegram-voice-bot\n   122→```\n   123→\n   124→## Managing the Service\n   125→\n   126→**Stop the bot:**\n   127→```bash\n   128→launchctl stop com.user.telegram-voice-bot\n   129→```\n   130→\n   131→**Restart the bot:**\n   132→```bash\n   133→launchctl stop com.user.telegram-voice-bot\n   134→launchctl start com.user.telegram-voice-bot\n   135→```\n   136→\n   137→**Disable auto-start:**\n   138→```bash\n   139→launchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.user.telegram-voice-bot.plist\n   140→```\n   141→\n   142→**View logs:**\n   143→```bash\n   144→tail -f logs/bot.log\n   145→tail -f logs/launchd.err.log\n   146→```\n   147→\n   148→## Troubleshooting\n   149→\n   150→### Bot doesn't respond\n   151→- Check token in `.env` file\n   152→- Check logs: `cat logs/bot.log`\n   153→- Ensure bot is running: `ps aux | grep bot.py`\n   154→\n   155→### Whisper takes too long\n   156→- First run downloads the model (~140MB for base)\n   157→- Consider using \"tiny\" model for faster processing\n   158→- Change in `.env`: `WHISPER_MODEL=tiny`\n   159→\n   160→### Voice messages not processing\n   161→- Check you've selected a project first with `/pick`\n   162→- Ensure Whisper model downloaded successfully\n   163→- Check audio directory permissions\n   164→\n   165→### Auto-start not working\n   166→- Check launchd logs: `tail logs/launchd.err.log`\n   167→- Verify plist syntax: `plutil ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.user.telegram-voice-bot.plist`\n   168→- Ensure full paths in plist file\n   169→\n   170→## Usage Flow\n   171→\n   172→1. **On your phone:** Open Telegram, message your bot\n   173→2. **Create project:** `/new Shopping List`\n   174→3. **Select project:** `/pick 001`\n   175→4. **Send voice notes:** Just record and send\n   176→5. **On laptop:** Find transcriptions in `projects/project-001-shopping-list/notes.md`\n   177→\n   178→## Notes\n   179→\n   180→- Bot processes queued messages when laptop comes online\n   181→- Voice files are deleted after transcription\n   182→- All data stays local on your laptop\n   183→- Projects are numbered sequentially (001, 002, etc.)\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existin